{"uid":"d8579172e5a163d0","name":"DS_12N RJCR RFC callback with Version header returns 400","fullName":"functional-tests.tests.callbacks.test_RTP_callback_with_version_header#test_rfc_callback_DS_12N_RJCR_with_version_header","historyId":"35a7804f5677e8f2948fc3b9452d0aa3","time":{"start":1784271184359,"stop":1784271188091,"duration":3732},"description":"\nDS_12N RJCR RFC callback sent with the Version header must be rejected with 400.\nThe RTP must remain in RFC_SENT (transition to ERROR_CANCEL must not happen).\n\nFlow:\n1. Activate payer, send RTP, trigger cancel via GPD DELETE → RFC_SENT\n2. Build a valid DS_12N RJCR payload\n3. POST to RFC callback endpoint WITH Version header\n4. Verify 400 is returned with the expected error body\n5. Verify RTP status is still RFC_SENT\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>DS_12N RJCR RFC callback sent with the Version header must be rejected with 400.<br />\nThe RTP must remain in RFC_SENT (transition to ERROR_CANCEL must not happen).</p>\n<p>Flow:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Activate payer, send RTP, trigger cancel via GPD DELETE → RFC_SENT</li>\n<li>Build a valid DS_12N RJCR payload</li>\n<li>POST to RFC callback endpoint WITH Version header</li>\n<li>Verify 400 is returned with the expected error body</li>\n<li>Verify RTP status is still RFC_SENT</li>\n</ol>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[{"name":"_session_faker","time":{"start":1784270839252,"stop":1784270839310,"duration":58},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"stepsCount":0,"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentStep":false},{"name":"rtp_consumer_access_token","time":{"start":1784271182743,"stop":1784271183263,"duration":520},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"stepsCount":0,"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentStep":false},{"name":"rtp_reader